dcterms:description: A pivotal surveillance system that broadcasts the aircraft’s position, velocity, and other information to the ground station and surrounding aircraft. The data recorded from ADS-B systems are susceptible to various irregularities due to multiple reasons, including antennas’ blind zones, signal jamming, and multipath interference.
dcterms:title: ADS-B Data
